sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_059_CSMS
    Note over CP,CS: Remote Start Transaction with Charging Profile
    Note over CP,CS: Table 182, Section 3.19.4, Pages 156-157/176
    Note over CP,CS: Prerequisite: Central System supports Smart Charging feature profile

    CS->>CP: 1. RemoteStartTransaction.req
    Note left of CS: idTag: <Configured valid IdTag><br/>connectorId: <Configured ConnectorId><br/>chargingProfile.chargingProfilePurpose: TxProfile<br/>chargingProfile.transactionId: <Omitted><br/>First chargingSchedulePeriod.startPeriod: 0<br/>recurrencyKind: <Omitted><br/>chargingProfileKind: Absolute or Relative<br/>[If Absolute: validFrom, validTo,<br/> startSchedule, duration all present]<br/>[If Relative: startSchedule <Omitted>]

    CP-->>CS: 2. RemoteStartTransaction.conf
    Note over CP: status: Accepted

    CP->>CS: 3. Authorize.req
    Note right of CP: idTag: <Same as step 1>

    CS-->>CP: 4. Authorize.conf
    Note over CS: idTagInfo.status: Accepted

    Note over CP,CS: [The charging cable is plugged in]

    CP->>CS: 5. StatusNotification.req
    Note right of CP: status: Preparing<br/>connectorId: <Same as step 1>

    CS-->>CP: 6. StatusNotification.conf

    CP->>CS: 7. StartTransaction.req
    Note right of CP: idTag: <Same as step 1><br/>connectorId: <Same as step 1>

    CS-->>CP: 8. StartTransaction.conf
    Note over CS: status: Accepted

    CP->>CS: 9. StatusNotification.req
    Note right of CP: status: Charging<br/>connectorId: <Same as step 1>

    CS-->>CP: 10. StatusNotification.conf

    Note over CS: Result: The Central System has started<br/>a transaction on the Charge Point and<br/>accepts the transaction that is started<br/>on the Charge Point.
